HEADWORD: Dapple
<hw>Dap"ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>depill</ets> a spot, a dot, a dog with spots over the eyes,
<ets>dapi</ets> a pool, and E. <ets>dimple</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of the
spots on a dappled animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He has . . . as many eyes on his body as my gray mare hath
<qex>dapples</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir P. Sidney.</qau></rj></p>

